- (i1 @ (i2 - i3)) + (i4 @ i5)
- (i1 + i2) @ i3 - i4 @ i5
- (i1 @ i2) + (i3 @ i4) - i5 @ i6
- (i1 + (i2 @ (i3 - i4))) @ i5
- (i1 @ i2 + i3) - (i4 @ i5) + i6

Each of these is a different way to combine the variables using the allowed operations.

I can also consider using the transpose in various places:

- (i1.T + i2) @ i3
- i1 @ (i2.T - i3)
- (i1 + i2.T) @ (i3 - i4)
